The paper deals with the problem of fairly dividing a heterogeneous cake between players, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves analyzing the social welfare of different cake division methods, which can be seen as a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.AI). The use of asymptotically-tight bounds suggests that the paper may involve some mathematical analysis, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
